                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.79693/8–3046: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-09-09T12:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 9, 1946—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>727. For attention Powell. Panam<note n="26" xml:id="d971fn26">Pan American World
                        Airways System.</note> just advises that airport Hong Kong inadequate for
                    larger planes and company doubts if it can serve Hong Kong in foreseeable
                    future. You will therefore disregard that part Deptel 708 Sept 4 which suggests
                    putting Hong Kong on route 2 and Canton on route 3 without optional interchange,
                    endeavoring to retain original language granting optional privilege at Canton
                    and Hong Kong on both routes.</p>
                <p>Sent to Nanking; repeated to Shanghai as Deptel 1603.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clayton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
